article_title: Walgreens Buys More Drugstores While Expanding Lab Services For Obamacare

article_metadata.description: Walgreen Co., said it would buy North Carolina drugstore chain Kerr Drug a day after announcing a new relationship to bring quicker lab tests into its stores via Theranos Inc. as the retailer expands its primary care role to prepare for the launch of the Affordable Care Act.
